The paper deals with efficient coding for multi-source networks, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses multicast and broadcast problems, which are related to network information (cs.NI) and source coding (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a novel notion of separation of source and network coding, which is related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and computer communication (cs.CC) sub-categories.
